### Searching Using Pipes ###
- How to search the contens of files
- What pipes are and how to use them


## Grep command
This helps to display lines matching a pattern

# example of use
grep pattern file
[pattern] -> the pattern is what we are wanting to search

# options
-i -> Search ignoring case
-c -> count number of occurences in a file
-n -> display a number of ocurrence with line numbers
-v -> print lines that don't match

## file command
# example of use
file file_name -> Display file type


